{
  "stem": "20142.9",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "For whatever they needed, I responded in a way that one, I have to show the gratitude of being-- having such family.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And, he passed away and his wife passed away quite a long time ago.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But I'm in contact with their grandchildren, because both of the cousins that I had passed away.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They introduced me to such a good life in the United States, as seeing such famous show with [INAUDIBLE], South Pacific, and the other shows that are still living with me.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I'm very proud of it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "There are very few people that perhaps can speak about the family, and the [? openness ?] and the [? friendliness, ?] and the way that we were received.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "A month--",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My brother remain in Belgium to finish his studies.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He survived as PO-- German POW, as a Polish POW in Germany in Stalag XI-A.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "This camp was chosen by the Red Cross as a-- a-- a-- a pictures of a prisoner of the war, the Germans could not touch it, despite of the fact there were a number of Jews in there, among them.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they were very, very careful about it.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And but fortunately, when the American frontier approach and reach the camp, many of these soldiers joined the US armed forces and fought alongside with them until the end of the war.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And then he returned back to Belgium, not realizing that perhaps I am survived.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But I had-- he had a feeling that I would somehow survive and be able to meet.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And after we exchanged the letters, he was on the way to convention in Prague, Czechoslovakia, for the gathering of textile engineers.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we met unfortunately in-- [?in a?] most unexplainable place like Nuremberg in Germany.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But it was worthwhile.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
